stringi Package installation & building


ICU4c
=====

On Linux:

cd /tmp
wget http://download.icu-project.org/files/icu4c/51.1/icu4c-51_1-src.tgz
tar -zxvf icu4c-51_1-src.tgz
cd icu/source/
./configure
make
sudo make install     # as root


Perhaps this also will be required:

sudo [edit_cmd] /etc/ld.so.conf

or:

sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libicuuc.so.51.1 /usr/lib    # or .so.XX.XX (check!)
sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libicui18n.so.51.1  /usr/lib
sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libicudata.so.51.1  /usr/lib
sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libicuio.so.51.1 /usr/lib
sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libicule.so.51.1 /usr/lib
sudo ln -s /usr/local/lib/libiculx.so.51.1 /usr/lib

Then update ld-database/cache:

sudo ldconfig



On Fedora Linux:

   you may try with `yum install libicu-devel`
   however, it may give you an outdated version of the ICU library
   therefore, it is not recommended



Get stringi from GitHub
=======================

cd /tmp
git clone https://github.com/gagolews/stringi.git
R CMD build stringi
R CMD INSTALL stringi_VERSION.tar.gz
